13 Sec. 1. 20 V.S.A. § 4652 is amended to read:
14 § 4652. AUTHORIZATION TO ENTER INTO AGREEMENTS
15 PURSUANT TO 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) AND 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i)
16 (a) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, only the Governor, in
17 consultation with the Vermont Attorney General upon approval from the
18 General Assembly as set forth in subsection (b) of this section, is authorized to
19 enter into, modify, or extend an agreement pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or
20 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i).
