1 (b) Notwithstanding subsection (a) of this section, a State, county, or
2 municipal law enforcement agency is authorized to enter into an agreement
3 pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i) when necessary to
4 address threats to the public safety or welfare of Vermont residents arising out
5 of a declaration of a State or national emergency
6 (1) The Governor shall not enter into an agreement pursuant to 8 U.S.C.
7 § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i) without prior approval from the General
8 Assembly.
9 (2) Not fewer than 60 days before the General Assembly may vote on a
10 proposed agreement pursuant to subdivision (1) of this subsection, the
11 Governor shall:
12 (A) provide the General Assembly with:
13 (i) the full text of the proposed agreement; and
14 (ii) an analysis of the potential fiscal, social, and legal impacts of
15 the agreement; and
16 (B) hold one or more public hearings in order to inform and gather
17 input from Vermonters, including immigrant advocacy organizations, on the
18 proposed agreement.
19 (3) No agreement pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i)
20 shall be entered into if the General Assembly is not in session.
